# Next.js App Structure

The project uses Next.js App Router for page routing and layout management.

## Key Pages

- [app/page.tsx](mdc:proflasher/src/app/page.tsx): Home page
- [app/chat/page.tsx](mdc:proflasher/src/app/chat/page.tsx): Main flashcard generation interface
- [app/settings/](mdc:proflasher/src/app/settings/): Application settings

## API Routes

- [app/api/llm/](mdc:proflasher/src/app/api/llm/): AI model interaction endpoints
- [app/api/anki/](mdc:proflasher/src/app/api/anki/): Anki operations and management

## Layout Structure

- [app/layout.tsx](mdc:proflasher/src/app/layout.tsx): Root layout with header and global styling
- Uses the Inter font from Google Fonts
- Includes a header component from [components/Header.tsx](mdc:proflasher/src/components/Header.tsx)

## Routing Pattern

The application follows Next.js App Router conventions:
- Each page is defined by a `page.tsx` file
- Route parameters are defined with `[param]` folders
- API routes are defined in `route.ts` files
- Shared layouts are defined in `layout.tsx` files
